      "content": "# Vaccine Intent & Trust Questionnaire\n\n## Section A: Vaccine Intent (Items 1-5)\n\n**Item 1:** How likely are you to receive a COVID-19 vaccine in the next 6 months?\n- [ ] Very unlikely\n- [ ] Unlikely\n- [ ] Neutral\n- [ ] Likely\n- [ ] Very likely\n\n**Item 2:** I plan to get vaccinated against COVID-19.\n- [ ] Strongly disagree\n- [ ] Disagree\n- [ ] Neither agree nor disagree\n- [ ] Agree\n- [ ] Strongly agree\n\n**Item 3:** Vaccination is the best way to protect myself and my family from COVID-19.\n- [ ] Strongly disagree\n- [ ] Disagree\n- [ ] Neither agree nor disagree\n- [ ] Agree\n- [ ] Strongly agree\n\n**Item 4:** I would recommend the COVID-19 vaccine to friends and family members.\n- [ ] Strongly disagree\n- [ ] Disagree\n- [ ] Neither agree nor disagree\n- [ ] Agree\n- [ ] Strongly agree\n\n**Item 5:** What is the main barrier preventing you from getting vaccinated? (Select all that apply)\n- [ ] Safety concerns\n- [ ] Lack of time\n- [ ] Distrust of health authorities\n- [ ] Religious or personal beliefs\n- [ ] Already had COVID-19\n- [ ] No barrier; I plan to get vaccinated\n\n## Section B: Trust in CDC (Items 6-10)\n\n**Item 6:** I trust the CDC to provide accurate information about vaccines.\n- [ ] Strongly disagree\n- [ ] Disagree\n- [ ] Neither agree nor disagree\n- [ ] Agree\n- [ ] Strongly agree\n\n**Item 7:** The CDC has my best interests in mind when making vaccine recommendations.\n- [ ] Strongly disagree\n- [ ] Disagree\n- [ ] Neither agree nor disagree\n- [ ] Agree\n- [ ] Strongly agree\n\n**Item 8:** The CDC communicates vaccine safety information clearly and honestly.\n- [ ] Strongly disagree\n- [ ] Disagree\n- [ ] Neither agree nor disagree\n- [ ] Agree\n- [ ] Strongly agree\n\n**Item 9:** I trust scientific evidence more than personal anecdotes about vaccine safety.\n- [ ] Strongly disagree\n- [ ] Disagree\n- [ ] Neither agree nor disagree\n- [ ] Agree\n- [ ] Strongly agree\n\n**Item 10:** The CDC's vaccine guidance has changed too much to be reliable.\n- [ ] Strongly disagree\n- [ ] Disagree\n- [ ] Neither agree nor disagree\n- [ ] Agree\n- [ ] Strongly agree\n\n## Section C: Primary Information Sources (Items 11-14)\n\n**Item 11:** Where do you primarily get information about vaccines? (Select one)\n- [ ] CDC website or official health agencies\n- [ ] Healthcare provider (doctor, nurse)\n- [ ] Social media (Facebook, Twitter, TikTok, etc.)\n- [ ] News media (TV, newspapers, online news)\n- [ ] Friends and family\n- [ ] Alternative health websites\n- [ ] Religious or community organizations\n\n**Item 12:** How often do you actively seek out vaccine information?\n- [ ] Never\n- [ ] Rarely\n- [ ] Sometimes\n- [ ] Often\n- [ ] Very often\n\n**Item 13:** I feel well-informed about vaccine effectiveness and safety.\n- [ ] Strongly disagree\n- [ ] Disagree\n- [ ] Neither agree nor disagree\n- [ ] Agree\n- [ ] Strongly agree\n\n**Item 14:** Social media has influenced my views about vaccines.\n- [ ] Strongly disagree\n- [ ] Disagree\n- [ ] Neither agree nor disagree\n- [ ] Agree\n- [ ] Strongly agree\n"
